How acn I change the argtypes for the disabled button to show a true/false switch? 
To change the argTypes for the disabled button to show a true/false switch instead of a checkbox, you can modify the `disabled` argType in your Button.stories.tsx file. Storybook offers a "boolean" control type which renders as a checkbox by default, but you can specify the "inline-radio" or "radio" control type to make it appear as a true/false switch.

Here's how to update the `disabled` argType:

```tsx
disabled: {
    control: 'inline-radio', // Change from 'boolean' to 'inline-radio'
    options: [true, false],  // Explicitly define the options
    description: "Deaktiverer knappen",
    table: {
        type: { summary: "boolean" },
        defaultValue: { summary: false },
    },
},
```

This modification will display the disabled option as a true/false radio button pair instead of a checkbox. The "inline-radio" control type will show the options side by side, creating a switch-like interface for toggling between true and false.

If you want the same for the "loading" property, you can apply the same change to that as well.
I want a switch saying true/false
To display a true/false switch (toggle) for the `disabled` property instead of radio buttons, you should use the `'boolean'` control type with the `switched` display option. Here's how to update your argTypes:

```tsx
disabled: {
    control: { 
        type: 'boolean',
        labels: {
            true: 'True',
            false: 'False'
        }
    },
    description: "Deaktiverer knappen",
    table: {
        type: { summary: "boolean" },
        defaultValue: { summary: false },
    },
},
```

Some Storybook versions also support a more direct approach:

```tsx
disabled: {
    control: 'boolean',
    description: "Deaktiverer knappen",
    table: {
        type: { summary: "boolean" },
        defaultValue: { summary: false },
    },
},
```

If you want a more explicit toggle-style switch, there's no built-in control for this in Storybook, but the standard boolean control usually renders as a checkbox which functions as a toggle.

Make sure you're using a recent version of Storybook (7.x+) for the best control options. If the boolean control doesn't render as a switch, you might need to update your Storybook version or customize the control panel.
I get the "Set boolean" button. Not a switch.

If you're seeing a "Set boolean" button instead of a proper switch toggle, this is a known issue in some Storybook versions. Let's try a more specific approach to get a proper switch control:

```tsx
disabled: {
    control: {
        type: 'boolean',
    },
    description: "Deaktiverer knappen",
    table: {
        type: { summary: "boolean" },
        defaultValue: { summary: false },
    },
},
```

If that doesn't work, another approach is to use a select control with true/false options:

```tsx
disabled: {
    control: {
        type: 'select',
        options: [false, true],
        labels: {
            [false]: 'False',
            [true]: 'True',
        }
    },
    description: "Deaktiverer knappen",
    table: {
        type: { summary: "boolean" },
        defaultValue: { summary: false },
    },
},
```

For Storybook 7.x, you might also try:

```tsx
disabled: {
    control: {
        type: 'boolean',
        presetColors: true,
    },
    description: "Deaktiverer knappen",
    table: {
        type: { summary: "boolean" },
        defaultValue: { summary: false },
    },
},
```

If none of these options work to give you a proper switch, it might be a limitation of your current Storybook version, and you may need to either update Storybook or use one of these workarounds.
