I want the children text of the button to be capitalized only on the first button on the first word.
To capitalize only the first word of the button's text, you can add a CSS class that applies the CSS text-transform property specifically to do this. Here's how to modify your Button.module.css:

1. Add a new CSS class that handles the capitalization of just the first letter:

```css
.capitalizeFirst {
    display: inline-block;
}

.capitalizeFirst::first-letter {
    text-transform: uppercase;
}
```

This approach uses the `::first-letter` pseudo-element to apply capitalization only to the first letter of the content.

Your updated CSS file would look like this (I'm showing just the addition, not replacing your entire CSS):

```css
.button {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin: 0;
    border: 0;
    outline: 0;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: all 150ms ease-out;
    cursor: pointer;
}

/* Add this new class */
.capitalizeFirst {
    display: inline-block;
}

.capitalizeFirst::first-letter {
    text-transform: uppercase;
}

/* Rest of your CSS remains unchanged */
```

Then in your Button component, you would need to wrap the children text in a span with this class. Your Button component would need to be updated to use this class.

Note: This approach assumes your button text is plain text. If your button children include complex components or HTML, you might need a different approach.
