Key changes made:

1. Added a `capitalizeFirstLetter` helper function that takes a string, splits it by spaces, capitalizes only the first letter of the first word, and rejoins the words.

2. Applied this function to the `children` text in both the loading and non-loading states.

3. Wrapped the capitalized text in a span to maintain proper styling.

This approach is better than using CSS because it gives you more precise control over exactly which part of the text gets capitalized, and it works regardless of how the button content is structured.

